    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1888-07-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1888-07-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="645"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d645">
                <head>No. 645.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Thompson</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Bayard</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Port au Prince Hayti</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1888-07-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">July</hi> 21, 1888</date>. (Received August
                        1.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 196.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: By the arrival of H. M. S. <hi rend="italic"
                        >Wrangler</hi> last evening and H. M. S. <hi rend="italic">Canada</hi> this
                    morning, we have at present in the harbor three British men-of-war, one French,
                    and one Dutch.</p>
                <p>I received this morning from the chief of the station at St. Nicholas Mole a
                    cable dispatch which read as follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>Impracticable this season, unless particulars of actual urgency
                            furnished. Bayard, Secretary of State, Washington.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Not only our citizens, but even natives and aliens, have expressed to me the hope
                    that one of our ships of war would also come, to show by such presence that no
                    question of autonomy would enter into the difficulties that seem surely to be
                    coming to this island in the near future.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">John E. W. Thompson.</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
